objects.description: Base Stratigraphic Horizon bounding the stratigraphic unit  in a context of a stratigraphic column (Denormalized information) and not in an context of a model which can have several interpretations. Expecting one single horizon.

objects.name: hasColumnStratigraphicHorizonTop
objects.description: Top Stratigraphic Horizon bounding the stratigraphic unit in a context of a reference stratigraphic column (Denormalized information) and not in an context of a model which can have several interpretations. Expecting one single horizon.

objects.name: hasDepositionGeometryType
objects.description: The reference to the deposition geometry type (Energistics RESQML DepositionMode) of this StratigraphicUnitInterpretation. RESQML BUSINESS RULE: The deposition mode for a geological unit MUST be consistent with the boundary relations of a genetic boundary. If it is not, then the boundary relation declaration is retained.

objects.name: hasDomainType
objects.description: Describes the domain of the interpretation: Depth, Time, Mixed

objects.name: hasFeature
objects.description: The reference to a local rock volume feature, to which this interpretation is associated.

objects.name: hasFeature
objects.description: Reference to the Feature the Interpretation refers to. The actual type of the target is specified in the specialisation, i.e. the type, which includes this schema fragment.

objects.name: hasGeologicUnitShapeType
objects.description: The relationship to a GeologicUnitShapeType like sheet, dyke, dome, mushroom, channel and more.

objects.name: hasLithologyType
objects.description: The relationship to a LithologyType, corresponding to Energistics GeologicUnitComposition.

objects.name: hasResource
objects.description: The SRN which identifies this OSDU Artefact resource.

objects.name: hasRole
objects.description: The SRN of this artefact's role.

objects.name: hasStratigraphicRoleType
objects.description: The reference to the stratigraphic role type (Energistics RESQML StratigraphicUnitKind) for this StratigraphicUnitInterpretation.

focusObject.name: AbstractInterpretation
focusObject.description: The group of properties shared by different kinds of interpretations
